tasks.description:
Create the page-level component and wire it into the `PAGE_COMPONENTS` lookup so the new `/dev/settings` route renders without a 'Page not found' state. The page starts as an empty `PlaygroundPageLayout` that Phase 3 fills with showcases.

## Files

### Create ‚Äî `apps/client/src/dev/pages/SettingsPage.tsx` (~20 lines)

Follow `apps/client/src/dev/pages/ComponentsPage.tsx` exactly:

```tsx
import { PlaygroundPageLayout } from '../PlaygroundPageLayout';
import { SETTINGS_SECTIONS } from '../playground-registry';

/** Settings dialog system gallery for the dev playground. */
export function SettingsPage() {
  return (
    <PlaygroundPageLayout
      title="Settings"
      description="Settings dialogs, individual tabs, loading and empty states, and primitives."
      sections={SETTINGS_SECTIONS}
    >
      {/* Showcases added in Phase 3 */}
    </PlaygroundPageLayout>
  );
}
```

Note: do NOT import `SettingsShowcases` yet ‚Äî it does not exist. Phase 3 task 3.1 imports it.

### Modify ‚Äî `apps/client/src/dev/DevPlayground.tsx`

The file currently has a `PAGE_COMPONENTS` lookup that maps page IDs to React components. Add two lines.

#### Step 1 ‚Äî Import

Add to the existing block of `import { ... } from './pages/...'` lines:
```ts
import { SettingsPage } from './pages/SettingsPage';
```

#### Step 2 ‚Äî Register in `PAGE_COMPONENTS`

Find:
```ts
const PAGE_COMPONENTS: Record<string, React.ComponentType<PlaygroundPageProps>> = {
  // ... existing entries
  tables: TablesPage,
};
```

Add:
```ts
const PAGE_COMPONENTS: Record<string, React.ComponentType<PlaygroundPageProps>> = {
  // ... existing entries
  tables: TablesPage,
  settings: SettingsPage,
};
```

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `apps/client/src/dev/pages/SettingsPage.tsx` exists and exports a default-named `SettingsPage` function
- [ ] `DevPlayground.tsx` imports `SettingsPage` and registers it under the `'settings'` key in `PAGE_COMPONENTS`
- [ ] Visiting `/dev/settings` in the browser shows the page header ("Settings") with an empty body and the (currently empty) TOC sidebar ‚Äî no console errors
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/dev/__tests__` passes ‚Äî none of the existing tests should fail (they're data-driven from the registry)
- [ ] Sidebar shows a new "Settings" item in the "App Shell" group with the lucide `Settings` icon

## Dependencies

Depends on tasks 2.1, 2.2, 2.3 (all the registry plumbing must exist for the page to render correctly).

Replace the empty `PlaygroundPageLayout` body in `SettingsPage.tsx` with `<SettingsShowcases />` so the Settings playground page actually renders content.

## File to modify

`apps/client/src/dev/pages/SettingsPage.tsx`

## Change

Replace the file body with:

```tsx
import { PlaygroundPageLayout } from '../PlaygroundPageLayout';
import { SETTINGS_SECTIONS } from '../playground-registry';
import { SettingsShowcases } from '../showcases/SettingsShowcases';

/** Settings dialog system gallery for the dev playground. */
export function SettingsPage() {
  return (
    <PlaygroundPageLayout
      title="Settings"
      description="Settings dialogs, individual tabs, loading and empty states, and primitives."
      sections={SETTINGS_SECTIONS}
    >
      <SettingsShowcases />
    </PlaygroundPageLayout>
  );
}
```

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `SettingsPage.tsx` imports `SettingsShowcases` from `../showcases/SettingsShowcases`
- [ ] `<SettingsShowcases />` is rendered as the only child of `<PlaygroundPageLayout>`
- [ ] Visiting `/dev/settings` shows all six sections rendered in order
- [ ] TOC sidebar lists all six sections under their categories
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes

## Dependencies

Depends on task 3.1 (the showcase file must exist). This is a trivial follow-up but kept as a separate task because it represents the moment the page goes from empty to live.
